verbose_text: After the AIC selection procedure, a further model selection process (XREF_FIG, Step 6), using partial (marginal) F-tests (the extra sum of squares principle), was used to test whether model parameters within the reduced model explained sufficient amounts of model variability (significance level alpha < 0.05) to provide a parsimonious model : a variable was removed if its omission did not significantly reduce the variability explained by the model (i.e. account for significant variability compared with the residual variability).
